folder: Fort Schuyler & U.S. Army Reservation & Third Quadrangle., Bronx, NY
text:
Fort Schuyler United States Army Reservation: Laborers are seen working on top of the northeast wall of the fort's third quadrangle under the supervision of the W.P.A. This is part of the general improvement operations being conducted on the reservation in connection with its lease by the War Department to the State of New York for nautical educational purposes.

April 27, 1936.

Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
title: Bronx: Fort Schuyler - U.S. Army Reservation - Third Quadrangle.

folder: Fort Schuyler & U.S. Army Reservation & Third Quandrangle., Bronx, NY
text:
Fort Schuyler United States Army Reservation: W.P.A. workmen are seen working on top of the northeast wall of the fort's third quadrangle. This is part of general improvement activities being conducted under the sponsorship of the State of New York to whom the reservation was leased by the War Department for nautical educational purposes by an act of Congress.

April 27, 1936.

Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
title: Bronx: Fort Schuyler - U.S. Army Reservation - Third Quandrangle.

folder: Fort Schuyler & U.S. Army Reservation & Third Quadrangle., Bronx, NY
text:
Fort Schuyler United States Army Reservation: An interior view of the northeast wall of the third quadrangle of the fort, showing improvement activities being carried out by the W.P.A. The reservation was leased to the State of New York by the War Department for the purpose of conducting nautical education work.

March 31, 1936.

Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
title: Bronx: Fort Schuyler - U.S. Army Reservation - Third Quadrangle.

folder: Fort Schuyler & U.S. Army Reservation., Bronx, NY
text:
Fort Schuyler United States Army Reservation: A view southward across the eastern extremity of the reservation and the East River, showing improvement activities being conducted by the W.P.A. as stipulated in legislation passed by Congress which permitted the War Department to lease the reservation to New York State for nautical educational purposes; improvements to be conducted under the state's sponsorship. In the background is the Queens shore.

Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.

March 31, 1936.
title: Bronx: Fort Schuyler - U.S. Army Reservation.

folder: Fort Schuyler & U.S. Army Reservation & eastern end., Bronx, NY
text:
Fort Schuyler United States Army Reservation: A view northeastward across the eastern extremity of the reservation toward Long Island Sound, showing improvement activities being carried on by the W.P.A. The reservation was leased in 1937 by the War Department to the State of New York for nautical educational purposes to be carried out at the state's expense and under its sponsorship.

March 31, 1936.

Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
title: Bronx: Fort Schuyler - U.S. Army Reservation - eastern end.

folder: Fort Schuyler & U.S. Army Reservation & Third Quadrangle., Bronx, NY
text:
Fort Schuyler United States Army Reservation: A view of the north-east wall of the fort's third quadrangle. The W.P.A. is conducting general improvement activities under the sponsorship of the State of New York. The reservation was leased to the state by the War Department for the establishment of a merchant marine academy.

April 27, 1936.

Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.
